The title for Shah Rukh Khan and Anushka Sharma--starrer next is yet to be decided but the Imtiaz Ali film is already making a lot of news: After flooding internet with viral pictures from the exotic sets, reports now claim that the domestic rights of the film has already been sold for a whopping Rs 125 crore.

A poster of the yet-to-be-titled film starring Shah Rukh Khan and Anushka Sharma.

According to a Bollywood Hungama report, Narendra Hirawat of NH Studioz has acquired the domestic and overseas distribution rights of the film, tentatively titled The Ring, for a staggering Rs 100+ crores. Industry insiders claim that the deal is valued at approx Rs 125 crores, the report added.

